&quot;Dirty Tricks - Now this is a change worthy of a Mercenary. Procs almost all the time (since that resist bug whent away), can get multiple targets and the effects make a hefty difference. A real &quot;Get out of trouble&quot; card every 7 minutes. With this, I can actually stand a chance with buffed stealthers. Throw in IP/Purge, and the battle is mine. Over all, great change. The best thing out of the patch for mercenarys, and maybe the whole intire thing. The only problem right now, is the lack of information. When it goes off, it makes a wind-spell noise. Because there's often tons of other noises, i can't hear if it goes off or not. A message saying he was effected (even when you effect him over and over again) would help a bunch in determining weather I should hit someone else or stay here. I don't really see any more 'needed' changes to this ability, but it's always nice to add things to it (maybe cause damage output to be lowered when using aswell as its current ability. Throwing dirt in their eyes would make it tougher to hit us, and when you do hit, it won't hurt as much since you can't really see what or who you're hitting. Though this isn't a nessessary change, it isn't overpowered and gives us a slightly better edge. I'v also never liked the idea that our &quot;key&quot; ability was based on defense. Something that can be real usefull is based on defense for an offensive person. With the damage reduction, I know that I get some effect out of it, and not a chance-effect).&quot;<br>
<br>
Great change. I'm glad I can finally rely on it now. <p>&quot;We will never be what Mythic promised we would when DAoC started, we might as well adapt or delete.&quot; -Avandor<br>
