<br>
TW - Stackable Damage Add &amp; Immunity to Melee Crits (both offensive &amp; defensive bonus, especially against Beserkers and people with high crit rate)<br>
<br>
DT - Increased Fumbles (&quot;aggressively defensive&quot;, since we have to be attacking something to have it work.  defensive bonus doesn't directly effect us, it's projected defense on our target's target)<br>
<br>
Frenzy - 100% Crits, 0 Defense (potentional for most offensive, with defense negation for all that attack)<br>
<br>
Kind of a raw deal, really.  Everything is in the right spirit, but things have become out of balance.  Granted DT can negate a person's offensive bonus (see Berserkers), but really when you think about it, it's really only geared for fast attackers, sure it's devasting on a Pole/Spear/2 handed attacker if they do fumble, but if they don't, well, it's completely useless.  At least TW still has the passive bonus if they miss, get stunned, etc.  If a Zerk or Merc gets stunned/rooted while using their abilities, that's it, no effect, and in the Berserker's case, they're worse off.<br>
<br>
I do like that DT isn't Purgeable now, that perhaps is the best change outside of the timer.  But I think that the effect could use some tweaking... how about this.<br>
<br>
What if DT gave a Mercenary a passive chance to force a fumble to any attacker (maybe within block radius), and gave our attacks a small, stackable bleed component or perhaps a small debuff?  As if as a reaction, the Mercenary was able to counter attack with dirt in the eyes, and our low blows hit sensitive areas of our enemies.<br>
<br>
However, if they make this change, or a change like it, then it's only fair that Berserkers have Frenzy changed: remove the defensive penalty, and even add in an absorbtion bonus, maybe with a absorbtion penalty cooldown.<br>
<br>
Thoughts? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vasagh>Vasagh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#000000>(6/27/03 4:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=262.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dirty tricks change</span><hr size=1> Frenzy is much more powerful than dirty tricks because it works on both casters/melee classes and has the potential to double your damage and kill a target faster.<br>
